cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC

This paper proposes a method for compressing deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves pruning connections in the network, which is a form of network optimization and can also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of splicing to avoid incorrect pruning, which is a form of network architecture design and can be categorized under neural engineering (cs.NE) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
